beer.beer_description:
Pouring a turbid pale yellow color into your glass, it explodes with notes of Sauvignon Blanc, apricot, mango, and juicy citrus.

To say that our experience at Garston Hops in the Southland of New Zealand had an impact on us would be an understatement.   This chance encounter marked the culmination of an unforgettable and impressionable odyssey through the land of the long white cloud. Here, we discovered a hop character entirely unique in its vibrancy and complexity.  Brewed with both Garston Nelson and Garston Rakau, Magic of Garston pours a turbid pale yellow color into your glass and explodes with notes of Sauvignon Blanc, apricot, mango, and juicy citrus. Wow!  As fans of Tree House and our hoppy beer, we hope beers such as this will stoke a flame of passion about the future because we will continue to pursue new and innovative experiences such as Magic
